---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Is ER a Scrabble Word? Yes — Valid in TWL & SOWPODS (2 Points)"
  description="ER is a valid Scrabble word in both TWL and SOWPODS, scoring 2 points (E=1, R=1). It's an interjection expressing hesitation. Learn strategy for playing common tiles effectively."
  keywords="is er a scrabble word, er scrabble, er valid scrabble, er points scrabble, er interjection, two letter words scrabble er, common tile strategy scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Article", "headline": "Is ER a Scrabble Word? Yes — Valid in TWL & SOWPODS (2 Points)", "description": "ER is a valid Scrabble word in both TWL and SOWPODS, scoring 2 points. An interjection expressing hesitation.", "datePublished": "2026-06-23", "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" }, "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" }, "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-er-a-scrabble-word" } })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": [ { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is ER a valid Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes — ER is valid in both TWL (Tournament Word List, North America) and SOWPODS (International/Collins). It scores 2 points (E=1, R=1) and is an interjection expressing hesitation or uncertainty, similar to 'um' or 'uh'. It uses two of the most common tiles in Scrabble." } }, { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many points is ER worth in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "ER scores 2 points in Scrabble (E=1, R=1). Both tiles are 1-pointers, making ER a low-scoring but highly useful word. On a Double Word square, ER scores 4. Its real value is tactical — dumping common tiles while creating hook and crossword opportunities." } }, { "@type": "Question", "name": "When should I play ER in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Play ER when you need to dump common tiles to improve your rack balance, when you want to create crossword opportunities for future turns, or when premium squares are accessible. ER is also excellent for parallel plays — both E and R connect with many letters to form 2-letter crosswords." } } ] })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/two-letter-words/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Two-Letter Words</a>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is ER a Scrabble Word?</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-23">June 23, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Yes — ER is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS. It scores just 2 points, but its real power lies in its tiles. E and R are two of the most common letters in the bag (12 E's and 6 R's), so you'll see ER opportunities constantly. As an interjection expressing hesitation ("er, I'm not sure..."), it's a legitimate word that helps manage your rack when common tiles pile up.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-green-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-950/30 to-emerald-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-green-500/70">✓ VALID</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">ER</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-green-300 font-semibold mb-3">2 points · E=1, R=1 · Interjection: hesitation</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Valid in both TWL (North American) and SOWPODS (International). An interjection expressing hesitation or uncertainty. Uses two of the most abundant tiles in Scrabble — you'll have ER opportunities every game.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">TWL ✓</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">North America</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">SOWPODS ✓</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">International</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">12+6</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Tiles in Bag</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Common Tiles, Common Opportunity</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The bag contains <span class="text-white font-medium">12 E tiles and 6 R tiles</span> — that's 18 tiles that can form ER. You'll have E+R on your rack frequently. ER isn't about scoring big (2pts is minimal). It's about <span class="text-white font-medium">rack management</span>: dumping common tiles to draw better ones, while setting up hooks and crosswords for your next turn.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy: When to Play ER</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Rack balance:</span> If your rack has 3+ vowels or duplicate common letters, playing ER dumps 2 tiles and draws 2 fresh ones. Better rack = better next turn.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Create crossword lanes:</span> Place ER where it opens premium squares for your next play. The letters E and R are among the most connectable — E forms 2-letter words with almost every consonant.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Parallel play powerhouse:</span> E connects with: AE, BE, DE, FE, HE, ME, NE, OE, PE, RE, WE, YE. R connects with: AR, ER, OR. This means ER placed parallel can score bonus points from crosswords.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hook extensions:</span> ER extends to ERE, ERG, ERN, ERR, ERS. Front hooks: HER, PER, SER. Many high-value words end in -ER (BIKER, MAKER, POKER). Building opportunities abound.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">ER Premium Square Scoring</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Base Score</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">E or R on DL</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">E or R on TL</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ER on DW</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Words That End in -ER</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MAKER</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">POKER</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">QUAKER</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">19pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MIXER</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-oe-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is OE a Scrabble Word? Wind Off the Faroe Islands</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/is-em-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is EM a Scrabble Word? Typographic Unit (4pts)</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/most-useful-two-letter-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Most Useful Two-Letter Words in Scrabble</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up required</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
